messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Primary language: Go (Golang)

Primary development framework: Gin (github.com/gin-gonic/gin)

Evidence and explanation:
- The repository contains go.mod, go.sum and .go source files (hello.go, doc.go, etc.), confirming this is a Go project.
- go.mod lists dependencies including github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.8.1 and github.com/jinzhu/gorm, showing the use of Gin as the HTTP framework and GORM as the ORM.
- hello.go imports "github.com/gin-gonic/gin" and its main() calls gin.Default(), defines route groups (r.Group("/api")), uses middleware (v1.Use(users.AuthMiddleware(...))) and r.Run(), which are canonical Gin usage patterns.

Additional context: this is the Golang/Gin RealWorld example app (implements REST routes, auth, and CRUD), so Gin is the primary web framework while GORM is used for database/model work.
